  "prompt": "How do I delete my own question from Quora?",
  "response": "Here's how to delete your question on Quora:\n\n1.  **Go to the Question:** Navigate to the question you want to delete.  You can find it on your profile, in your feed, or through a search.\n\n2.  **Find the \"...\" Menu:** On the question page, look for a small ellipsis (three dots) icon, usually located near the top right of the question, or below it. Click on it.\n\n3.  **Select \"Delete\":**  A dropdown menu will appear.  Choose the \"Delete\" option from this menu.\n\n4.  **Confirm Deletion:** Quora will likely ask you to confirm your decision. There might be a pop-up window or a confirmation message.  Click \"Delete\" again (or whatever button confirms the deletion) to proceed.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Once a question is deleted, it's gone.**  You cannot retrieve it.\n*   **Think before deleting:** If your question has valuable answers, consider whether deleting it is the best option. The answers might be helpful to others, even if you no longer need the information.\n*   **Alternatives to Deletion:** Instead of deleting, you might consider editing the question to improve it, or disengaging from it. If there are problematic answers, you can report them.\n*   **Moderation:** If a question violates Quora's policies, it may be deleted by Quora's moderation team, regardless of who asked it.\n\nIf you're having trouble finding the \"...\" menu or the \"Delete\" option, double-check that you're logged into the account that asked the question. If you still can't find it, there might be a temporary glitch, or the question might have been flagged/moderated. You can try contacting Quora support if you believe there's an error.\n",
